<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IModuleHandle" Title="IModuleHandle interface" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.PlatformBindings">PlatformBindings</PageRef> ->
    IModuleHandle
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Declaration">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[class IModuleHandle;]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>IModuleHandle</TypeRef> interface represents an owning reference to a dynamically loaded renderer plugin module.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
      Renderer plugin loading helpers use module handles to keep a plugin library loaded while objects allocated by that plugin are still alive.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Warning">
      <Paragraph>
        Do not unload a renderer plugin library while its graphics device enumerator, devices, renderer, or resources are still alive. Keep the relevant <TypeRef>IModuleHandle::unique_ptr</TypeRef> alive until those objects have been destroyed.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Members">
    <SubSection Title="Initialization methods">
      <FunctionMemberList>
        <FunctionMemberListEntry Visibility="Public" Name="Clone" PageName="cobalt.graphics.IModuleHandle.Clone">
          Creates another owning handle to the same module.
        </FunctionMemberListEntry>
